The paper proposes a method for open-domain question answering using Wikipedia as the knowledge source, which involves document retrieval and machine comprehension of text. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Deep Learning (cs.DL). Among these, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the task of natural language processing and information retrieval, which are key components of the proposed approach. cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.DL are also relevant as they involve machine learning techniques that are used in the paper's model.
